Metinvest Considers Buying Ukrainian Steel Plants, Interfax Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-06-09T15:38:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/metinvest-considers-buying-ukrainian-steel-plants-interfax-says.html
Metinvest Holding LLC is studying the
possibility of buying Ukraine’s Alchevskiy and Dniprovsky steel
plants, as well as considering the purchase of a stake in their
owner Industrial Union of Donbass, Interfax Ukraine reported.  The Kiev-based newswire cited a person it didn’t identify.  Metinvest is 75 percent-owned by System Capital Management
Group, held by Ukraine’s richest man  Rinat Akhmetov .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  